**Job Title:** Architect/Engineer Project Manager at the Public Building Division

**Location:** Lugano, Switzerland - Public Competition at Lugano (TI)

**CAPITOLATO DI CONCORSO PUBBLICO PER L'ASSUNZIONE DI UN/A ARCHITETTO/A O INGEGNERE/A CAPOPROGETTO PRESSO LA DIVISIONE EDILIZIA PUBBLICA DELLA CITTÀ DI LUGANO**

The Municipality of Lugano is opening a public competition for the appointment of an architect/engineer project manager at the Public Building Division of the City of Lugano, in accordance with the Organic Regulation of the City of Lugano's collaborators (ROCCL) and the present competition charter.

**General Requirements**

- Unblemished conduct;
- Physical and mental fitness for the function.

**Specific Requirements**

- Bachelor's degree in architecture or engineering with academic or SUP or equivalent education;
- Proven professional experience related to the function;
- Ability to manage technical and financial aspects of projects;
- Organizational, planning, control, analysis, and decision-making skills;
- Listening, interpersonal communication, mediation, negotiation, and customer service skills;
- Precision, reliability, speed, respect for deadlines, and confidentiality in work;
- Flexibility, autonomy, initiative, and innovation spirit, quality orientation, practical sense, and responsibility, ability to adapt and sustain high work rates;
- Strong writing, synthesis, and relational skills;
- Ability to work independently and in a team;
- Willingness to continue professional training (updating and professional improvement);
- Familiarity with main computer programs (Windows environment, MS Office package, CAD, etc.);
- Excellent knowledge of the Italian language (comprehension and speaking at C1 level or equivalent or higher);
- Category B driving license.

**Preferred Qualifications**

- Proven experience in managing technical and financial aspects and coordinating complex projects in the public and/or private construction sector;
- Proven experience in the field of safety, energy efficiency, and sustainability;
- Proven experience in public procurement procedures;
- Knowledge of a second national language, French and/or German.

**Job Responsibilities**

Based on project planning, attributions, service needs, project objectives, and priorities set by supervisors, the project manager will manage activities related to project implementation, ensuring the correctness of processes, respect for costs, times, and quality. Specifically:

- Supervises and participates in setting up and verifying projects assigned to external agents, such as consultants and designers;
- Verifies the progress of works in all phases in relation to times, costs, and quality;
- Analyzes and resolves problems and reprograms activities accordingly;
- Collaborates in defining the project schedule with designers and contractors operating on the construction site;
- Conducts feasibility studies of projects, analyzing technical, economic, and procedural aspects;
- Collaborates in defining project objectives and requirements, ensuring quality, functionality, sustainability, and cost control;
- Organizes operational needs and plans the intervention, defining phases, priorities, times, and execution methods;
- Supervises the technical and financial management of the project, ensuring adherence to established estimates (continuous updating of financial accounting tables, analysis of new prices, pre-notifications of payments, etc.);
- Applies operational procedures and quality management, contributing to their constant development and improvement;
- Accompanies the inspection of individual works managed and collects technical documentation, archives it, and manages any defects and guarantees;
- Handles administrative and insurance practices autonomously (technical pre-notifications, reports, various correspondence, financial accounts, bid control, awards, etc.);
- Provides consultation, assistance, and information to customers;
- Maintains regular contact with internal and external partners to the Municipal Administration for all matters within their competence;
- Sets up Municipal Messages and assists the direct supervisor in drafting them;
- Informs supervisors periodically on the progress of projects in relation to times, costs, and quality.

**Additional Responsibilities**

- Other work assignments compatible with their function and skills may be conferred.

**Salary**

Annual salary (including 13th month and updated salary scale as of 01.01.2026). Grade XV (reference ROCCL function: public building architects/engineers), classes 16-17-18.

Class 16: min CHF 93,074.15 / max CHF 109,827.40
Class 17: min CHF 99,757.15 / max CHF 117,713.30
Class 18: min CHF 107,208.25 / max CHF 126,505.50

**Observations**

Within the aforementioned salary possibilities, the Municipality may recognize previously performed activity, if in accordance with the present charter, assigning one or more years of service in accordance with Article 39, paragraph 1, ROCCL.

The Municipal Administration offers the possibility of increasing professional skills and knowledge through internal and external training measures.

**Application Requirements**

Applications must be submitted electronically through the City of Lugano's online portal (https://egov.lugano.ch/). The Municipality will not consider applications and attachments sent through other channels (paper form, email, fax, etc.). The Human Resources Division remains at the disposal of those who do not possess a device (PC, tablet, smartphone, etc.) through which to apply (t. +41 58 866 70 32). Offers, accompanied by the following documents:

- Letter of presentation
- Curriculum vitae
- Recent photograph
- Study and work certificates
- Driving license

must be sent through the online portal by midnight on Monday, March 30, 2026.

In addition to the documents attached to the online application, it may be requested to present the extract of the judicial record for private individuals (if necessary, also the specific extract of the judicial record for private individuals) and the extract of the execution register.

**Municipality of Lugano**
**Department:** Public Administration
**Location:** Via Nizzola 5, 6900 Lugano, TI, Switzerland

